text: July unemployment rates ranged from 2.0% in SD to 5.5% in DC.
Q1 2024 real state GDP growth over the year ranged from 0.8% in IA and MS to 5.0% in TX.
Q1 2024 house price growth over the year ranged from -1.5% in DC to 12.8% in VT.
Among states, July average private weekly earnings ranged from NM’s $929 to WA’s $1,371.
Retail and trade jobs in July 2024 were above July 2019 levels in 24 states.
Every state and DC saw year-over-year retail GDP growth exceed 6% in real terms in Q1 2024.
GA’s unemployment rate has remained at or between 3.0% and 3.5% since September 2021.
Private jobs in July 2024 were below July 2019 levels in 5 states.
Between Q1 2018 and Q1 2024, MO’s real manufacturing GDP has grown from $42 billion to $50 billion.
NC’s annual house price growth has exceeded 5% every quarter since 2015.
